# Sakhi Suraksha API Tests
# Use REST Client extension in VS Code or copy to Postman

### 1. Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/health

### 2. API Info
GET http://localhost:5000/

### 3. Send OTP
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+919876543210"
}

### 4. Verify OTP (use the OTP from console logs)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+919876543210",
  "otp": "123456"
}

### 5. Create User Profile (replace TOKEN with JWT from verify-otp response)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/user/profile
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "phoneNumber": "+919876543210",
  "emergencyMessage": "I need help!",
  "voiceActivationEnabled": true
}

### 6. Trigger Emergency Alert
POST http://localhost:5000/api/emergency-alerts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "latitude": 28.6139,
  "longitude": 77.2090,
  "triggerType": "manual"
}

### 7. Get Emergency Alerts
GET http://localhost:5000/api/emergency-alerts
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### 8. Add Emergency Contact
POST http://localhost:5000/api/emergency-contacts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Mom",
  "phoneNumber": "+919876543211",
  "email": "mom@example.com",
  "relationship": "mother",
  "isPrimary": true,
  "canReceiveSMS": true,
  "canReceiveWhatsApp": true,
  "canReceiveCall": true
}

